05229nam a22007935i 9789814881661DE-B159720210621102733.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210621t20202020si     fo  d z      eng d  a97898148816617 a10.1355/97898148816612doi  a(DE-B1597)573835  a(OCoLC)1224278026  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  asicSG 7aBIO0100002bisacsh04a959.80350922231 aKusumaatmadja, Sarwono, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aSteering a Middle Course :bFrom Activist to Secretary General of Golkar /cSarwono Kusumaatmadja. 1aSingapore : bISEAS Publishing, c[2020] 4c©2020  a1 online resource (280 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tForeword by Senior Minister and Coordinating Minister for National Security, Singapore, Teo Chee Hean -- tA Testimonial for Steering a Middle Course By Dr Siti Nurbaya Bakar, Minister of the Environment and Forestry of Indonesia (2014–) -- tPreface -- tA Testimonial To Remain Unaffected by Power -- t1. A Clumsy Boy from Sentiong -- t2. Activism and Becoming a Politician -- t3. Full Time Politician and Outsider -- t4. True to the Middle Course -- tEpilogue -- tGlossary -- tBibliography -- tIndex -- tAbout the Author0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aBorn with motor impairment, Sarwono Kusumaatmadja grew up with low self-esteem. Yet, within this awkward, shy boy lay a steely resolve to overcome his weaknesses. It was this same resolve that propelled him to study at high school in the United Kingdom, thousands of miles from his native land. Navigating life on his own in the UK forged Sarwono into an independent and resilient individual; one who never flinched in the face of challenges, but also one who never wanted to play the hero either. His unique character and integrity acted like a magnet for opportunities back home in Indonesia. He was chosen to be Chairman of the University Student Council of the Bandung Institute of Technology even though he did not campaign for it. And when he made it into the national parliament, it was at the behest of the military. He then became Secretary General of Golkar, the country’s ruling party, without having to pull any strings. In taking on all the opportunities that came his way, Sarwono remained true to himself, which later meant saying no to President Soeharto when the latter tried to recruit him to be part of his inner circle.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 4aBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Political.2bisacsh1 aBakar, Siti Nurbaya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHean, Teo Chee, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWitoelar, Wimar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2020z9783110704594oZDB-23-PLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311068959408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP ROW Ebook Package English 2020z978311069630140uhttps://doi.org/10.1355/978981488166140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789814881661423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789814881661.jpg  a978-3-11-068959-4  ISEAS Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-069629-5  DG Plus PP P